Share this on WhatsAppWasiu Ayinde has gone under the knife again, for the umpteenth time in over a decade.
According to an Instagram post by Bolaji Basia on Saturday night, the fuji maestro had a minor surgery.
“I still give thanks to almighty God for the success,” he wrote.
He last had a throat operation in a Canadian hospital in 2019, following the one he had about a year earlier—for some respiratory complications—in Canada.
